Package org.hms.services.appointment

Class AppointmentSchedule

java.lang.Object
org.hms.services.appointment.AppointmentSchedule
public class AppointmentSchedule extends Object
The AppointmentSchedule class is responsible for storing and managing a scheduling matrix which includes information about doctor IDs and their assigned time slots.

  • Field Details

    • matrix

      private String[][] matrix
      A 2D String array representing the scheduling matrix. This matrix holds information about doctor IDs and the corresponding time slots. The top row and leftmost column serve as headers for doctor IDs and time slots respectively.

  • Constructor Details

    • AppointmentSchedule

      public AppointmentSchedule(int numDoctors, int numTimeSlots)
      Constructs an AppointmentSchedule object with a specified number of doctors and time slots. The scheduling matrix is initialized with these dimensions, and the top-left cell is set as the header label.
      Parameters:
      numDoctors - the number of doctors to be included in the schedule
      numTimeSlots - the number of time slots to be included in the schedule

  • Method Details

    • setDoctorID

      public void setDoctorID(int col, String doctorID)
      Sets the ID of a doctor in the scheduling matrix.
      Parameters:
      col - An integer representing the column index where the doctor ID should be placed.
      doctorID - A String representing the ID of the doctor to be set in the specified column.

    • setTimeSlot

      public void setTimeSlot(int row, String timeSlot)
      Sets the time slot string at the specified row in the schedule matrix.
      Parameters:
      row - the index of the row where the time slot should be set (0-based, excluding header)
      timeSlot - the time slot string to be inserted into the matrix

    • setSlot

      public void setSlot(int timeSlotRow, int doctorCol, String value)
      Sets a value for a specific time slot and doctor in the scheduling matrix.
      Parameters:
      timeSlotRow - the row index of the time slot (0-based)
      doctorCol - the column index of the doctor (0-based)
      value - the value to set in the slot

    • getDoctorID

      public String getDoctorID(int col)
      Retrieves the doctor ID at the specified column index in the scheduling matrix.
      Parameters:
      col - The index of the column to retrieve the doctor ID from, excluding the header cell.
      Returns:
      The doctor ID located at the specified column index.

    • getTimeSlot

      public String getTimeSlot(int row)
      Retrieves the time slot string at the specified row in the schedule matrix.
      Parameters:
      row - the row index from which to retrieve the time slot, 0-based
      Returns:
      the time slot string associated with the specified row

    • getSlot

      public String getSlot(int timeSlotRow, int doctorCol)
      Retrieves the value of a specific slot in the scheduling matrix.
      Parameters:
      timeSlotRow - The row index corresponding to the desired time slot (0-based).
      doctorCol - The column index corresponding to the desired doctor (0-based).
      Returns:
      The value stored in the specified slot of the scheduling matrix.

    • getMatrix

      public String[][] getMatrix()
      Retrieves the scheduling matrix containing doctor IDs and their assigned time slots.
      Returns:
      A 2D String array representing the schedule with doctor IDs and time slots.

    • setMatrix

      public void setMatrix(String[][] newMatrix)
      Updates the matrix with a new scheduling matrix.
      Parameters:
      newMatrix - The new scheduling matrix containing updated doctor IDs and time slot information.
